1
00:00:13,609 --> 00:00:15,920
(Jung Ryeo Won)

2
00:00:17,519 --> 00:00:19,820
(Wi Ha Jun)

3
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:29,900
(Scriptwriter: Park Kyeong Hwa)

4
00:00:30,299 --> 00:00:32,869
(Director: Ahn Pan Seok)

5
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:43,940
(The Midnight Romance in Hagwon)

6
00:00:50,649 --> 00:00:52,020
Were you guys meeting up here?

7
00:00:52,289 --> 00:00:54,089
(Episode 15)

8
00:00:54,090 --> 00:00:55,090
No.

9
00:00:59,929 --> 00:01:01,329
It was nothing serious.

10
00:01:07,999 --> 00:01:09,069
Please sit down.

11
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:23,250
It's nothing.

12
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:32,190
Well, you guys had a tough day today.

13
00:01:32,429 --> 00:01:34,759
He must have been a little shaken up.

14
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,600
Enough to make him cry?

15
00:01:38,729 --> 00:01:39,770
Him?

16
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:41,369
Well...

17
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,369
He had nothing to do with it. I...

18
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,869
I must have been tired.

19
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,410
I have no excuse for what happened recently.

20
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,308
If you want to hold anyone responsible, that should be me.

21
00:01:51,309 --> 00:01:52,350
Ms. Seo.

22
00:01:52,809 --> 00:01:53,850
It's nothing like that.

23
00:01:54,819 --> 00:01:56,020
I was just tired. That's all.

24
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,149
You want me to believe that?

25
00:02:00,419 --> 00:02:01,990
I'm asking you to let it slide.

26
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:05,089
- But you're crying. - Yes, I cried like a baby.

27
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:08,860
So let's just move on.

28
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:16,039
Did you have dinner?

29
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:17,669
Yes.

30
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:21,979
I need to use the restroom.

31
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,479
- Excuse me. - Yes.

32
00:02:29,919 --> 00:02:32,150
Could you give us some food?

33
00:02:32,519 --> 00:02:34,859
Something easy to swallow would be nice.

34
00:02:35,019 --> 00:02:36,019
Sure.

35
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,729
By the way,

36
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:42,160
are there any cigarettes...

37
00:02:42,259 --> 00:02:44,430
other customers left behind? If so, could you spare a few?

38
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,470
- Here. - Gosh.

39
00:02:52,009 --> 00:02:53,310
I should have called you.

40
00:02:54,509 --> 00:02:55,609
I made you wait a long time, didn't I?

41
00:02:57,609 --> 00:02:58,949
You did well, getting through today.

42
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,380
Let's have some food first.

43
00:03:02,579 --> 00:03:04,690
I heard you kicked out a student during your class.

44
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,160
Why did you do it?

45
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:15,259
Because I didn't want to teach him.

46
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,799
Don't be emotional.

47
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,139
Think about the damage the academy is facing.

48
00:03:23,169 --> 00:03:25,009
Each student is important to us now.

49
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:29,138
If you kick out all the students who are rude...

50
00:03:29,139 --> 00:03:30,210
Is that...

51
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:33,650
what you really want...

52
00:03:34,949 --> 00:03:35,979
to talk about now?

53
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:39,090
Will you answer me...

54
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,690
if I ask you why you're like this?

55
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:47,190
A lot of students think...

56
00:03:47,191 --> 00:03:49,198
academy instructors are beneath them.

57
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:50,460
Not that.

58
00:03:52,229 --> 00:03:53,630
Tell me what you really want to say.

59
00:03:55,039 --> 00:03:56,299
Tell me things like...

60
00:03:57,970 --> 00:03:59,238
how today was for you and so on.

61
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,969
I know that we don't have to go along...

62
00:04:00,970 --> 00:04:02,508
with their jokes, ignorance, or mockery, but...

63
00:04:02,509 --> 00:04:04,210
"Today had been a tough day."

64
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:08,279
"It was exhausting." Tell me stuff like that.

65
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,119
Being emotional won't help much.

66
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,120
"Jun Ho."

67
00:04:13,889 --> 00:04:15,789
"Putting up with the gossip was much harder than I thought."

68
00:04:16,989 --> 00:04:19,329
- Stuff like that. - Call the student tomorrow...

69
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,459
and apologize too.

70
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:22,030
"The students and the mothers..."

71
00:04:23,929 --> 00:04:25,200
"had no loyalty."

72
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:27,700
"I felt wronged and disappointed."

73
00:04:28,539 --> 00:04:29,570
Just tell me...

74
00:04:30,039 --> 00:04:31,140
things like this.

75
00:04:32,039 --> 00:04:33,369
Why are you talking to me like this?

76
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:37,308
You're the one who cried like a baby.

77
00:04:37,309 --> 00:04:38,450
But why are you patronizing me?

78
00:04:45,249 --> 00:04:47,089
The student you kicked out is famous for his attitude.

79
00:04:47,090 --> 00:04:49,059
- His father... - "This is all your fault."

80
00:04:52,729 --> 00:04:54,030
Say that.

81
00:04:59,530 --> 00:05:01,340
- "All day today..." - All day today...

82
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,739
All day today,

83
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:08,080
I wondered how it would've been if I were never your teacher.

84
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:10,539
That crossed my mind. So what?

85
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:15,179
How would it have been if we were around the same age?

86
00:05:15,679 --> 00:05:17,080
That's what I wondered. So what?

87
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:24,220
The student who had a crush on you. The prettiest girl in your school.

88
00:05:24,689 --> 00:05:26,330
"What if I were her?"

89
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,799
"Then people wouldn't have gossiped about us like this."

90
00:05:33,299 --> 00:05:36,400
"How different would it have been if I had a proper job?"

91
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:41,070
"Then my career wouldn't be ruined for dating someone from the office."

92
00:05:42,809 --> 00:05:43,809
Yes.

93
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,419
I thought this was so messed up.

94
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,419
I knew that I shouldn't expect loyalty in this neighborhood.

95
00:05:55,289 --> 00:05:57,559
But I still had to try to make something of myself in this field.

96
00:05:58,530 --> 00:06:00,989
So that made me feel really pathetic. So what?

97
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,299
Do you feel good now?

98
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,739
You can keep going.

99
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:16,039
Don't be ridiculous.

100
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:19,150
You were crying your eyes out when I got here.

101
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:21,850
You made me cower like a scared kid.

102
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:50,780
Thank you.

103
00:08:06,989 --> 00:08:08,520
Thank you, sir.

104
00:08:15,559 --> 00:08:17,600
(Night Flight)

105
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,470
(Closed)

106
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,978
Should I pour you a drink?

107
00:08:28,979 --> 00:08:30,010
Gosh.

108
00:08:38,989 --> 00:08:40,720
Then it's on me now.

109
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,820
Lucky me.

110
00:08:49,999 --> 00:08:51,259
Academy instructors...

111
00:08:52,229 --> 00:08:54,170
rarely get attached to students.

112
00:08:55,269 --> 00:08:57,739
Otherwise, it'd be too hard on them every year.

113
00:08:58,170 --> 00:09:00,340
You all say that.

114
00:09:01,170 --> 00:09:03,080
But my bar is the busiest during the graduation season.

115
00:09:04,009 --> 00:09:06,479
They must be lonely. They drink quite a lot.

116
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,889
That's their way of trying to forget the students quickly.

117
00:09:12,850 --> 00:09:14,790
They try their best not to be curious about them.

118
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:17,659
How much they grew up.

119
00:09:18,489 --> 00:09:20,060
What kind of person they've become.

120
00:09:20,690 --> 00:09:22,430
Wondering about that isn't up to us.

121
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,200
But...

122
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:27,629
I'm curious about Jun Ho, though.

123
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,570
I wonder how much he'd grow.

124
00:09:31,710 --> 00:09:32,909
He's already all grown up, though.

125
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,979
Gosh. I'm such a pathetic man.

126
00:09:38,649 --> 00:09:40,748
My academy is about to go down in flames.

127
00:09:40,749 --> 00:09:42,619
But I'm here, wondering about Jun Ho.

128
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:44,690
Gosh. Why do you say that?

129
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:46,618
Even during wartime,

130
00:09:46,619 --> 00:09:48,920
people still pursue art, fall in love,

131
00:09:49,290 --> 00:09:51,190
and compete in sports games.

132
00:09:51,389 --> 00:09:52,389
You're right.

133
00:09:55,229 --> 00:09:56,229
Okay.

134
00:10:12,909 --> 00:10:14,379
It will be spring soon.

135
00:10:15,249 --> 00:10:17,279
Gosh. Time flies.

136
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,988
New students will come in,

137
00:10:21,989 --> 00:10:24,619
and the year will go by quickly again.

138
00:10:25,930 --> 00:10:28,330
You've overcome all your hardships so far.

139
00:10:31,159 --> 00:10:32,229
Right.

140
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,869
As long as my instructors decide to continue teaching at my academy.

141
00:10:41,070 --> 00:10:43,080
(Night Flight)

142
00:10:44,850 --> 00:10:46,850
(X Force)

143
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:03,999
Don't do that.

144
00:11:05,729 --> 00:11:07,129
Using your coat as an umbrella...

145
00:11:07,369 --> 00:11:08,700
and running into the rain.

146
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:10,700
I won't do that with you.

147
00:11:32,159 --> 00:11:34,229
(Daechi Chase, Accepting new students)

148
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,440
Let's dry our clothes before we go. Please?

149
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,210
It'll be awful if you catch a cold.

150
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:53,409
Mind your own business.

151
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,149
Fine.

152
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,950
I'll tell you...

153
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,820
why I was crying like a pathetic fool.

154
00:12:21,609 --> 00:12:22,639
I'm sorry...

155
00:12:23,940 --> 00:12:25,109
for upsetting you.

156
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:29,050
But don't even think about how it would've been...

157
00:12:29,279 --> 00:12:30,550
if you weren't my teacher.

158
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:32,820
I had never imagined such a scenario.

159
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:36,389
Our age difference...

160
00:12:36,989 --> 00:12:39,460
or the prettiest girl in my school who had a crush on me...

161
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:41,389
Just forget all of that.

162
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:43,499
I don't even remember her name.

163
00:12:45,229 --> 00:12:46,229
I do.

164
00:12:47,769 --> 00:12:48,940
It was Cho Yoon Hee.

165
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:55,580
I heard Seoung Gyu and Ho Jae talk about that. So I knew.

166
00:13:00,479 --> 00:13:02,619
Tell me. Why did you cry?

167
00:13:07,090 --> 00:13:08,119
Jun Ho.

168
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:14,229
Mr. Lee.

169
00:13:18,369 --> 00:13:19,999
"Nothing scares me in this world."

170
00:13:21,129 --> 00:13:23,070
"Once I set my mind to it, I get it done."

171
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:26,810
I realized all of that was nothing but pathetic self-delusion.

172
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:32,050
I realized it only after seeing you getting torn apart by the vultures.

173
00:13:33,409 --> 00:13:35,680
I failed to see what would happen to you.

174
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,449
I deceived myself by hiding behind the argument...

175
00:13:40,450 --> 00:13:42,060
that all I needed was your love.

176
00:13:43,659 --> 00:13:45,190
I was embarrassed by everything I did.

177
00:13:48,029 --> 00:13:49,599
My mother researched every nook and corner of Daechi-dong...

178
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,700
and found you.

179
00:13:52,330 --> 00:13:54,970
I got my grades up thanks to you. But I acted like a big shot genius.

180
00:13:55,639 --> 00:13:56,739
That was just ridiculous.

181
00:13:58,239 --> 00:13:59,309
I acted like I accomplished...

182
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:01,209
something amazing by getting into a decent school.

183
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:02,279
That was just absurd.

184
00:14:03,340 --> 00:14:04,340
Jun Ho.

185
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:08,549
My parents and you were always ready to support me...

186
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:09,879
with complete confidence in me.

187
00:14:12,050 --> 00:14:13,550
The moment I left their safe nest,

188
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:16,589
a mere incident like this was enough to make me crumble.

189
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,690
That's how weak I was.

190
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:19,859
That crossed my mind.

191
00:14:21,830 --> 00:14:23,658
But in the midst of everything, when I heard...

192
00:14:23,659 --> 00:14:25,330
how you thought you were to blame for everything,

193
00:14:26,229 --> 00:14:27,570
it became clear to me.

194
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:30,869
That I hadn't...

195
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:36,080
grown up at all from the kid you met for the first time...

196
00:14:37,009 --> 00:14:38,210
in the classroom.

197
00:14:39,649 --> 00:14:40,710
That's...

198
00:14:42,649 --> 00:14:44,180
just how I am.

199
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:46,989
You say that's how you are.

200
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:49,619
But I wasn't able to change you even one bit...

201
00:14:51,359 --> 00:14:52,659
when I said I loved you.

202
00:14:59,369 --> 00:15:00,470
I must...

203
00:15:01,629 --> 00:15:04,070
get out of that small classroom from ten years ago.

204
00:15:06,409 --> 00:15:08,609
I read the books you gave me and wrote down what you told me.

205
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:11,239
I had enough compliments...

206
00:15:12,149 --> 00:15:15,009
and was adored enough by doing the things you told me.

207
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,749
Thank you.

208
00:15:24,420 --> 00:15:25,489
But...

209
00:15:28,999 --> 00:15:30,029
I...

210
00:15:31,129 --> 00:15:32,200
It's long overdue.

211
00:15:34,470 --> 00:15:35,570
Give it to me now.

212
00:15:37,769 --> 00:15:38,909
My well-deserved diploma.

213
00:15:48,050 --> 00:15:49,649
There's one more thing that's bothering me.

214
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:51,950
(Daechi Chase Hall of Fame)

215
00:15:58,190 --> 00:15:59,529
Before I joined the academy,

216
00:16:00,489 --> 00:16:01,930
I came to see you. Remember that?

217
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,330
This was the very place...

218
00:16:07,129 --> 00:16:08,229
you told me this.

219
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:11,399
Of course. The sky is the limit for you.

220
00:16:12,739 --> 00:16:14,310
I'll return what you said.

221
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,580
I don't need it. I don't need that encouragement.

222
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,979
You don't need to have such a desperate thought that...

223
00:16:20,249 --> 00:16:21,608
this is the only way you can make a living.

224
00:16:21,609 --> 00:16:22,979
I'm 35 years old.

225
00:16:23,879 --> 00:16:26,690
I'll support you even if you want to try out to become an idol star.

226
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,290
Let's go. I have a class in the morning.

227
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:33,460
(Daechi Chase Hall of Fame)

228
00:17:41,189 --> 00:17:43,230
I wondered how it would've been if I were never your teacher.

229
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:51,639
How would it have been if we were around the same age?

230
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:57,139
Didn't you get rained on on your way home?

231
00:19:00,969 --> 00:19:02,379
It started to pour down all of a sudden.

232
00:19:03,780 --> 00:19:06,280
Gosh. I told you there was no need to escort me home.

233
00:19:06,550 --> 00:19:08,010
You were stubborn for no reason.

234
00:19:08,209 --> 00:19:10,850
Gosh. Getting caught in the rain isn't a big deal.

235
00:19:12,949 --> 00:19:15,320
By the way, how's your throat?

236
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,959
You went pretty hard at the karaoke.

237
00:19:18,459 --> 00:19:20,629
So you don't know what it means to go hard.

238
00:19:21,389 --> 00:19:23,060
I didn't even show you half of my talent.

239
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,270
- Hey. - Hi.

240
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:37,639
I have class from 1pm to 4pm. Bye.

241
00:19:38,179 --> 00:19:39,609
- Gosh. - Hello.

242
00:19:39,810 --> 00:19:43,479
I didn't know you were on the phone. I wouldn't have interrupted you.

243
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:44,619
- I see. - Gosh.

244
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:47,448
It's hard to tell when people use wireless earbuds.

245
00:19:47,449 --> 00:19:48,889
It's fine.

246
00:19:50,159 --> 00:19:52,059
I guess you didn't have breakfast.

247
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:53,590
I didn't.

248
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:57,459
Gosh, it smells great.

249
00:19:58,699 --> 00:20:00,629
Let's pick some bread. It's on me.

250
00:20:03,100 --> 00:20:05,409
- It's a bribe. - To me?

251
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:09,040
If we're on the same side,

252
00:20:09,139 --> 00:20:11,040
I want to make a good impression on you.

253
00:20:12,179 --> 00:20:13,449
I teach social studies.

254
00:20:14,050 --> 00:20:16,520
I ought to be on good terms with Korean instructors.

255
00:20:18,580 --> 00:20:19,590
Come in.

256
00:20:50,179 --> 00:20:51,179
Gosh.

257
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:53,350
Ms. Seo...

258
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:56,888
had been doing a very good job of crossing selling...

259
00:20:56,889 --> 00:20:58,189
other subjects.

260
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:01,090
She always gave out flyers during her class.

261
00:21:01,629 --> 00:21:03,999
She scheduled the classes perfectly, so they had time to eat...

262
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,159
before other classes here.

263
00:21:06,429 --> 00:21:07,429
Gosh.

264
00:21:08,669 --> 00:21:10,000
She always thought of everything.

265
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:14,070
When we were going head-to-head with Choisun Academy,

266
00:21:14,510 --> 00:21:17,040
some instructors weren't happy with the advertisement.

267
00:21:17,639 --> 00:21:20,350
She promised them to bring students to them to calm them down.

268
00:21:21,409 --> 00:21:24,179
So you're telling me instructors who had been close to Ms. Seo...

269
00:21:24,679 --> 00:21:26,949
are facing the biggest damage?

270
00:21:30,159 --> 00:21:31,959
How ironic.

271
00:21:33,389 --> 00:21:35,600
If there's anything that can comfort you,

272
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:39,129
