00:38:44,159 --> 00:38:46,460
Going this far to ruin the person you had feelings for...

541
00:38:47,790 --> 00:38:48,988
is hardly sane.

542
00:38:48,989 --> 00:38:50,029
You're lucky...

543
00:38:51,230 --> 00:38:52,799
not to have even known this feeling.

544
00:38:56,500 --> 00:38:58,069
Fellowship, friendship, or loyalty.

545
00:38:59,639 --> 00:39:00,868
I bet you've never had to be in someone's life...

546
00:39:00,869 --> 00:39:02,069
masking your love for something above.

547
00:39:03,610 --> 00:39:04,610
I have.

548
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:07,779
I moved out of my parents' house...

549
00:39:09,009 --> 00:39:10,420
to live closer to Ms. Seo.

550
00:39:14,420 --> 00:39:15,719
When you started dating,

551
00:39:16,719 --> 00:39:18,420
she should've told me.

552
00:39:19,690 --> 00:39:21,560
She should've stopped me from orbiting around her.

553
00:39:24,529 --> 00:39:27,100
She should've thought about how humiliated I'd feel.

554
00:39:28,799 --> 00:39:30,669
What's humiliating...

555
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:32,900
about orbiting around the person you like?

556
00:39:34,670 --> 00:39:36,908
Blowing up her world because of it...

557
00:39:36,909 --> 00:39:38,079
- is more shameful. - Shut it...

558
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:39,080
if you don't know any better.

559
00:39:39,081 --> 00:39:40,150
That...

560
00:39:42,049 --> 00:39:43,319
is how criminals think.

561
00:39:54,830 --> 00:39:55,830
Lee Jun Ho.

562
00:39:58,259 --> 00:39:59,429
You'd better watch your words.

563
00:39:59,759 --> 00:40:02,000
"You made me do something this bad."

564
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:05,569
That's how criminals justify themselves.

565
00:40:08,839 --> 00:40:10,679
Who are you trying to teach?

566
00:40:12,739 --> 00:40:14,750
I also used to be one of your instructors.

567
00:40:15,009 --> 00:40:17,980
I'm just a guy who's warning the person...

568
00:40:20,049 --> 00:40:21,150
bullying his girlfriend.

569
00:40:24,119 --> 00:40:25,690
I'm meeting Ms. Woo.

570
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:28,929
But I wanted to confirm something first.

571
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:31,830
Yoon Ji Seok and Woo Seung Hui...

572
00:40:32,529 --> 00:40:34,330
only recently joined forces.

573
00:40:34,699 --> 00:40:36,299
I had to test your loyalty.

574
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:39,239
I wanted to know how quickly you'd tell her...

575
00:40:40,239 --> 00:40:41,540
about what happened this morning...

576
00:40:41,739 --> 00:40:42,869
and how serious you are...

577
00:40:46,580 --> 00:40:49,049
about ruining Seo Hye Jin and her career.

578
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:56,250
I have my answer.

579
00:40:58,060 --> 00:40:59,089
I do.

580
00:41:20,009 --> 00:41:22,080
(Daechi Chase)

581
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:34,929
(Vice-director's Office)

582
00:41:44,339 --> 00:41:45,698
(Daechi Chase)

583
00:41:45,699 --> 00:41:46,739
It's Mr. Lee.

584
00:41:48,139 --> 00:41:49,639
Can you take this, Min Ji?

585
00:41:50,739 --> 00:41:51,909
- I'll be on standby. - Okay.

586
00:41:59,020 --> 00:42:00,020
Where are you going?

587
00:42:00,319 --> 00:42:01,389
Hey.

588
00:42:02,319 --> 00:42:04,989
Oh, I have a lunch appointment.

589
00:42:05,960 --> 00:42:06,960
With whom?

590
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:09,488
(Daechi Chase)

591
00:42:09,489 --> 00:42:10,529
Vice-director Woo Seung Hui.

592
00:42:11,699 --> 00:42:13,299
Don't go there. Knowing your temper...

593
00:42:17,469 --> 00:42:19,540
(Prepare for the KSAT with Daechi Chase.)

594
00:42:22,509 --> 00:42:23,540
Is that them?

595
00:42:24,310 --> 00:42:25,339
They're still together.

596
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:39,790
I know you're afraid.

597
00:42:40,130 --> 00:42:41,560
Gosh. I'm not afraid.

598
00:42:41,989 --> 00:42:44,259
Everything from Mr. Pyo to Choisun Academy.

599
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,769
It'd feel like everything you planned became a boomerang...

600
00:42:47,770 --> 00:42:49,270
and hit you in the throat.

601
00:42:50,270 --> 00:42:52,900
This must be your first time getting caught up in gossip.

602
00:42:54,509 --> 00:42:56,040
I get why you're shying away.

603
00:42:56,909 --> 00:42:59,909
So eat a hearty lunch...

604
00:43:00,549 --> 00:43:01,909
and teach your class.

605
00:43:03,779 --> 00:43:06,650
You haven't yet told me what you said to Lee Myeong Jun.

606
00:43:07,250 --> 00:43:08,350
I will when I get back.

607
00:43:10,889 --> 00:43:11,960
But...

608
00:43:16,429 --> 00:43:18,529
I find this a bit upsetting.

609
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:25,600
See you later.

610
00:43:47,830 --> 00:43:48,830
Come in.

611
00:43:50,860 --> 00:43:52,400
- Hey. - Hello.

612
00:44:09,750 --> 00:44:11,920
I made sure I was on time. Did you wait for long?

613
00:44:12,449 --> 00:44:13,449
No.

614
00:44:14,420 --> 00:44:15,819
I got here early.

615
00:44:16,350 --> 00:44:18,219
The thought of seeing you excited me.

616
00:44:19,759 --> 00:44:20,960
Thank you for calling.

617
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:22,889
Don't say that.

618
00:44:23,060 --> 00:44:25,230
You sent me an invitation first.

619
00:44:27,469 --> 00:44:29,928
You could've just called if you wanted to see me.

620
00:44:29,929 --> 00:44:31,900
You didn't have to go through Myeong Jun.

621
00:44:32,739 --> 00:44:34,940
I thought it was likely you'd refuse to see me.

622
00:44:35,909 --> 00:44:38,139
Oh, dear. How come?

623
00:44:38,980 --> 00:44:42,009
Because Lee Jun Ho must seem useless.

624
00:44:43,049 --> 00:44:45,350
Because I'm just a kid who follows Seo Hye Jin around.

625
00:44:45,949 --> 00:44:48,219
You must've felt a pang of guilt too.

626
00:44:48,650 --> 00:44:50,389
Considering what you did to Ms. Seo.

627
00:44:53,259 --> 00:44:54,630
I wanted to make my presence known...

628
00:44:55,790 --> 00:44:58,259
and test Myeong Jun and Ji Seok's loyalty.

629
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:00,869
So I went through the hassle of doing this.

630
00:45:02,230 --> 00:45:03,299
You don't...

631
00:45:03,839 --> 00:45:06,469
really intend to side with Myeong Jun?

632
00:45:06,799 --> 00:45:07,869
I hope to.

633
00:45:08,639 --> 00:45:11,179
It would be hard, though, since we'd be up against you.

634
00:45:16,250 --> 00:45:17,279
How amazing.

635
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:21,219
I feel almost jealous.

636
00:45:23,020 --> 00:45:24,020
Of me?

637
00:45:24,889 --> 00:45:27,230
Of your youth, to be exact.

638
00:45:28,889 --> 00:45:31,400
Love gives you strength and energy, doesn't it?

639
00:45:32,130 --> 00:45:33,159
Yes.

640
00:45:34,670 --> 00:45:37,139
How young, tender, and sweet of you.

641
00:45:38,040 --> 00:45:39,969
But you're a seasoned veteran.

642
00:45:40,409 --> 00:45:42,068
Armed with intellect and strategy.

643
00:45:42,069 --> 00:45:44,339
Goodness. Well, thank you.

644
00:45:48,080 --> 00:45:49,509
So...

645
00:45:51,920 --> 00:45:53,650
Instead of resorting to this,

646
00:45:56,219 --> 00:45:58,319
won't it be better to just make a clean break?

647
00:46:00,989 --> 00:46:03,130
Is that why you wanted to see me?

648
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:05,799
To give me advice?

649
00:46:06,330 --> 00:46:07,429
To plead with you.

650
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:10,469
This academy means more to me than my alma mater.

651
00:46:13,069 --> 00:46:14,770
I don't think I can do that.

652
00:46:15,610 --> 00:46:17,440
The adults have their reasons.

653
00:46:17,909 --> 00:46:20,509
Don't you care for your juniors' respect or support?

654
00:46:23,150 --> 00:46:25,049
How about you show...

655
00:46:25,420 --> 00:46:29,150
some more care and support for your girlfriend?

656
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:34,529
Hye Jin looked so frail. A gust of wind could break her bone.

657
00:46:36,060 --> 00:46:37,500
How much longer...

658
00:46:37,699 --> 00:46:40,900
are you planning to watch her stay up at night to teach kids?

659
00:46:43,170 --> 00:46:44,469
She gave up what she wanted to do...

660
00:46:44,839 --> 00:46:48,569
and worked her whole life to support her family.

661
00:46:49,040 --> 00:46:51,079
Just when she thought she could take things slow,

662
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:52,980
she was facing her end as an academy instructor.

663
00:46:53,110 --> 00:46:54,948
She doesn't have the stamina she used to,

664
00:46:54,949 --> 00:46:56,679
and she definitely isn't as smart.

665
00:46:58,619 --> 00:47:02,289
Wouldn't a decent man succeed as soon as possible...

666
00:47:02,290 --> 00:47:03,789
so he could take care of...

667
00:47:03,790 --> 00:47:05,489
the woman he loved?

668
00:47:08,690 --> 00:47:09,690
Guess what?

669
00:47:11,130 --> 00:47:12,560
When you applied to join us,

670
00:47:13,259 --> 00:47:15,130
I gave your test lecture the highest mark.

671
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:17,639
What?

672
00:47:18,100 --> 00:47:20,868
Your age, degree, stability, and potential.

673
00:47:20,869 --> 00:47:23,509
I thought highly of all of it, including your ambitious nature.

674
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:26,940
I see.

675
00:47:27,049 --> 00:47:28,250
Now I'm thinking...

676
00:47:29,150 --> 00:47:31,119
it would be a waste to leave you behind.

677
00:47:34,949 --> 00:47:36,020
Don't you think...

678
00:47:36,949 --> 00:47:38,290
you called me a bit too late for that?

679
00:47:40,730 --> 00:47:41,860
To be honest,

680
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:45,529
I thought trying to persuade you would be a waste of time.

681
00:47:46,659 --> 00:47:48,929
But you had the guts to come see me, so I'm having second thoughts.

682
00:47:50,900 --> 00:47:52,170
You should make the switch.

683
00:47:52,369 --> 00:47:55,509
You have great aspirations.

684
00:47:58,739 --> 00:48:01,080
I don't think Choi Hyung Sun would approve of me...

685
00:48:01,380 --> 00:48:02,449
because of the Heewon High incident.

686
00:48:02,480 --> 00:48:04,480
I can put in a good word for you, of course.

687
00:48:12,759 --> 00:48:14,529
Can I take off my coat?

688
00:48:14,929 --> 00:48:16,889
- Yes, of course. - Thanks.

689
00:48:25,639 --> 00:48:26,869
You really know nothing about this?

690
00:48:27,869 --> 00:48:29,610
You weren't behind it?

691
00:48:29,810 --> 00:48:31,480
What on earth...

692
00:48:31,509 --> 00:48:33,009
was in the email Jun Ho sent you?

693
00:48:33,610 --> 00:48:35,279
It really wasn't something you two set up?

694
00:48:36,150 --> 00:48:37,179
Mr. Lee.

695
00:48:41,290 --> 00:48:42,319
His teaching notes.

696
00:48:43,219 --> 00:48:44,219
And materials.

697
00:48:44,790 --> 00:48:46,389
They won't be of much use to me, though.

698
00:48:54,270 --> 00:48:55,299
Why...

699
00:48:56,270 --> 00:48:57,270
Why did he do that?

700
00:48:59,369 --> 00:49:00,639
Why are you asking me?

701
00:49:06,009 --> 00:49:07,850
He must want me to join him.

702
00:49:10,619 --> 00:49:11,619
Goodness.

703
00:49:12,520 --> 00:49:14,089
I'm going downstairs.

704
00:49:16,489 --> 00:49:17,489
What in the...

705
00:49:18,159 --> 00:49:19,489
Why would he...

706
00:49:25,830 --> 00:49:26,830
Gosh.

707
00:49:37,509 --> 00:49:38,509
Gosh.

708
00:49:39,779 --> 00:49:41,210
I should keep my wits about me.

709
00:49:43,880 --> 00:49:47,350
I just realized why people side with you...

710
00:49:47,719 --> 00:49:48,750
after just one meeting.

711
00:49:50,119 --> 00:49:52,119
- I can be quite persuasive, right? - Yes.

712
00:49:52,659 --> 00:49:55,388
Especially the part about being a decent man.

713
00:49:55,389 --> 00:49:56,790
Gosh, that was just...

714
00:49:58,199 --> 00:49:59,699
It really touched me.

715
00:50:01,900 --> 00:50:04,299
You shouldn't sneer when an adult talks.

716
00:50:05,170 --> 00:50:06,198
Fix that.

717
00:50:06,199 --> 00:50:08,810
I also saw why Victoria Academy went under.

718
00:50:11,580 --> 00:50:14,479
There's no need to talk about what we all know.

719
00:50:14,480 --> 00:50:15,509
You don't know.

720
00:50:16,650 --> 00:50:18,178
I'm not talking about Kim Hyun Tak's plan...

721
00:50:18,179 --> 00:50:19,650
to buy your academy at a bargain price.

722
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:25,460
Even if you were to be born again, you'd never be a good teacher.

723
00:50:26,589 --> 00:50:28,860
That's why you drove your academy to ruin.

724
00:50:29,889 --> 00:50:30,960
You really are young.

725
00:50:31,960 --> 00:50:34,329
You're talking about being a good teacher in this situation?

726
00:50:34,330 --> 00:50:37,239
"A decent man would bring his woman riches and honors."

727
00:50:38,270 --> 00:50:39,969
"Whether it means siding with the thieves,"

728
00:50:40,400 --> 00:50:43,069
"joining forces with a rat who spreads dirty rumors,"

729
00:50:43,270 --> 00:50:45,610
"or ruining the livelihoods of innocent others, do it."

730
00:50:46,940 --> 00:50:49,610
What would side with someone who talks gibberish like that?

731
00:50:51,580 --> 00:50:53,020
Nothing but dung flies.

732
00:50:56,089 --> 00:50:58,119
- Mind your manners. - Of course...

733
00:50:58,860 --> 00:51:00,689
everyone jumped ship at the first signs...

734
00:51:00,690 --> 00:51:02,560
that the academy was struggling.

735
00:51:03,429 --> 00:51:04,460
That's why you went down.

736
00:51:04,929 --> 00:51:06,000
You...

737
00:51:07,369 --> 00:51:09,730
- Can you stop using that... - I'm saying it on purpose.

738
00:51:11,600 --> 00:51:13,969
Because you'll go down in the future for the exact same reasons.

739
00:51:16,069 --> 00:51:17,139
Goodness.

740
00:51:17,779 --> 00:51:20,079
To think that the man Hye Jin ended up with...

741
00:51:20,080 --> 00:51:21,480
Is a pathetic kid.

742
00:51:23,350 --> 00:51:25,150
Is that what you said to Yoon Ji Seok too?

743
00:51:29,049 --> 00:51:31,318
I'm asking how your future...

744
00:51:31,319 --> 00:51:34,130
would benefit from people who fell for that.

745
00:51:34,929 --> 00:51:38,000
Even Myeong Jun's wondering whether or not to jump ship.

746
00:51:58,219 --> 00:51:59,949
Your emotions must be running high...

747
00:52:00,750 --> 00:52:02,549
because you're being attacked from all sides.

748
00:52:03,619 --> 00:52:06,219
You shouldn't make decisions when you're worked up.

749
00:52:06,920 --> 00:52:08,659
Okay? Go back...

750
00:52:09,389 --> 00:52:11,460
and reflect on your mistakes.

751
00:52:13,060 --> 00:52:14,069
"Reflect?"

752
00:52:15,670 --> 00:52:16,699
Me?

753
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:19,040
Goodness.

754
00:52:20,440 --> 00:52:23,569
Did I steal someone's teaching material...

755
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:26,178
or start rumors that Woo Seung Hui's toying with younger men...

756
00:52:26,179 --> 00:52:27,350
Have you lost your mind?

757
00:52:28,310 --> 00:52:29,310
Are you offended?

758
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:36,219
That's exactly what Ms. Seo's going through.

759
00:52:37,960 --> 00:52:39,360
Can you even imagine how it feels?

760
00:52:41,830 --> 00:52:44,759
Despite that, she's fighting not to stoop as low as you.

761
00:52:46,259 --> 00:52:49,130
That shows she is already a much better teacher than you.

762
00:52:50,699 --> 00:52:53,299
Eventually, she'll be surrounded by people, not dung flies.

763
00:52:54,739 --> 00:52:55,810
And you...

764
00:52:57,210 --> 00:52:58,480
will go down once more.

765
00:52:58,980 --> 00:52:59,980
Fine.

766
00:53:00,480 --> 00:53:02,549
Let's take this all the way.

767
00:53:02,710 --> 00:53:05,520
Some things you must experience to learn for yourself.

768
00:53:05,819 --> 00:53:08,190
You need to see what moves the world...

769
00:53:08,920 --> 00:53:10,588
the adults live in.

770
00:53:10,589 --> 00:53:13,489
Why haven't you learned anything from your experiences?

771
00:53:15,759 --> 00:53:17,230
Don't go down the same way.

772
00:53:18,199 --> 00:53:19,230
You can eat your lunch without me.

773
00:53:22,199 --> 00:53:25,040
You won't go down if you turn back now.

774
00:53:31,580 --> 00:53:33,679
Wait. Ms. Woo.

775
00:53:36,880 --> 00:53:37,880
Here.

776
00:53:39,679 --> 00:53:40,690
Don't forget this.

777
00:53:42,750 --> 00:53:44,420
You need it to look like an intellect.

778
00:53:45,759 --> 00:53:46,759
It's an important prop.

779
00:56:10,029 --> 00:56:13,940
(Vice-Director Woo Seung Hui)

780
00:56:17,270 --> 00:56:18,310
I'm in class.

781
00:56:21,679 --> 00:56:23,650
He thinks I'm stupid.

782
00:56:25,980 --> 00:56:27,049
Darn it.

783
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:42,029
Oh, gosh.

784
00:56:45,900 --> 00:56:46,969
My goodness.

785
00:56:49,440 --> 00:56:50,469
Hey.

786
00:56:53,179 --> 00:56:54,279
Jun Ho.

787
00:56:55,750 --> 00:56:57,679
Oh, gosh. What the...

788
00:56:58,750 --> 00:56:59,819
What are you doing here?

789
00:57:01,790 --> 00:57:03,350
- Gosh. - Are you ill or something?

790
00:57:03,989 --> 00:57:05,190
No.

791
00:57:05,759 --> 00:57:09,060
I came over to take a shower.

792
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:11,630
Why would you take a shower here?

793
00:57:12,860 --> 00:57:13,860
I'm sweating.

794
00:57:14,330 --> 00:57:15,400
What?

795
00:57:17,299 --> 00:57:18,500
You don't have a fever.

796
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:20,540
I have my reasons.

797
00:57:21,770 --> 00:57:23,670
I'll wash up.

798
00:57:23,770 --> 00:57:24,779
Okay.

799
00:57:27,139 --> 00:57:28,210
Oh, dear...

800
00:57:38,819 --> 00:57:39,819
Bye.

801
00:57:40,520 --> 00:57:42,130
You're leaving already? Without dinner?

802
00:57:43,159 --> 00:57:44,400
I have to go. It was a short visit.

803
00:57:46,199 --> 00:57:47,259
Sit down.

804
00:57:47,360 --> 00:57:48,900
I don't have the time. I have to go.

805
00:57:52,699 --> 00:57:53,799
Must you do this?

806
00:57:54,739 --> 00:57:58,009
Do you want me to visit Hye Jin and throw things around?

807
00:57:58,839 --> 00:57:59,839
Why...

808
00:58:02,580 --> 00:58:03,650
Leave.

809
00:58:06,020 --> 00:58:07,049
Mom.

810
00:58:07,819 --> 00:58:10,250
You said you had no time. Go.

811
00:58:21,630 --> 00:58:22,630
What's going on?

812
00:58:23,770 --> 00:58:25,500
I heard there are lots of good movies out.

813
00:58:26,799 --> 00:58:28,339
Let's watch one on my day off.

814
00:58:30,670 --> 00:58:33,179
I'll treat you to the hotel brunch you like too.

815
00:58:34,009 --> 00:58:35,009
What?

816
00:58:35,449 --> 00:58:37,178
And in the evening, we'll eat what you cook...

817
00:58:37,179 --> 00:58:39,350
and watch TV together. And then I'll stay the night.

818
00:58:40,549 --> 00:58:42,290
I'll wash the bean sprouts with you...

819
00:58:43,150 --> 00:58:44,219
and take you on a walk.

820
00:58:46,719 --> 00:58:49,929
I know you want to spend time and chat with me.

821
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:53,630
Sorry for being a jerk.

822
00:58:55,600 --> 00:58:57,130
What trick is this?

823
00:58:57,270 --> 00:58:58,500
It's not a trick.

824
00:58:59,139 --> 00:59:00,199
I want to do all that.

825
00:59:00,799 --> 00:59:01,810
As if you do.

826
00:59:05,710 --> 00:59:07,949
- But Mom. - What?

827
00:59:08,409 --> 00:59:10,250
Ms. Seo taught me all that.

828
00:59:11,380 --> 00:59:12,679
Darn you.

829
00:59:13,920 --> 00:59:15,049
Be generous with her.

830
00:59:15,319 --> 00:59:16,349
- You... - Okay.

831
00:59:16,350 --> 00:59:18,988
- I didn't hit you enough last time. - Okay.

832
00:59:18,989 --> 00:59:21,290
My goodness. You really...

833
00:59:35,940 --> 00:59:37,270
You'll eat all this?

834
00:59:38,110 --> 00:59:39,409
I missed lunch.

835
00:59:43,850 --> 00:59:45,580
Woo Seung Hui didn't buy you lunch?

836
00:59:45,819 --> 00:59:48,190
We made each other lose their appetites.

837
00:59:52,420 --> 00:59:53,460
But...

838
00:59:54,219 --> 00:59:57,060
What did you talk about that made you skip lunch?

839
00:59:58,199 --> 00:59:59,960
I told her I saw why her academy went down...

840
01:00:00,560 --> 01:00:01,670
and that she'd go down again.

841
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:03,029
What?

842
01:00:06,770 --> 01:00:09,869
I was going to be polite, but I changed my mind halfway.

843
01:00:10,810 --> 01:00:11,839
Why?

844
01:00:15,350 --> 01:00:17,580
Because she looked smug.

845
01:00:22,589 --> 01:00:25,690
I get that crushing us would make them feel good.

846
01:00:26,489 --> 01:00:28,730
Studying is boring, and the future is bleak.

847
01:00:29,360 --> 01:00:30,659
They don't care about the truth.

848
01:00:31,100 --> 01:00:32,900
Even less about the morals of academy instructors.

849
01:00:34,529 --> 01:00:37,799
They like enjoying the provocative and dirty nature of all this.

850
01:00:38,940 --> 01:00:41,210
How thrilling is it to watch someone successful go down?

851
01:00:41,839 --> 01:00:42,869
That hurts.

852
01:00:43,969 --> 01:00:45,409
Be gentle.

853
01:00:45,940 --> 01:00:46,940
Sorry.

854
01:00:49,949 --> 01:00:51,380
But Woo Seung Hui shouldn't do that.

855
01:00:53,179 --> 01:00:55,219
She shouldn't smile as she tries to buy people.

856
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:03,029
In time, everyone will forget about us.

857
01:01:03,730 --> 01:01:05,759
Moms will start sending their kids back to us.

858
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:08,770
They think they have the right to talk...

859
01:01:09,000 --> 01:01:10,029
because they pay.

860
01:01:11,199 --> 01:01:12,369
"I crushed you,"

861
01:01:13,469 --> 01:01:15,170
"but you can't ignore my demands."

862
01:01:15,909 --> 01:01:18,439
Yes. Like you said, in time...

863
01:01:18,440 --> 01:01:19,839
I don't plan to just wait...

864
01:01:20,040 --> 01:01:21,449
until time passes.

865
01:01:24,009 --> 01:01:27,480
I'll prove how clean and exact a person...

866
01:01:28,250 --> 01:01:29,290
you really are.

867
01:01:41,630 --> 01:01:43,670
What about the Gangnam building you want to buy?

868
01:01:45,270 --> 01:01:47,299
Hasn't your goal become a bit too shabby?

869
01:01:47,839 --> 01:01:49,769
A man who can't keep his relationship on track...

870
01:01:49,770 --> 01:01:52,409
can't own a building, let alone a studio apartment.

871
01:01:55,509 --> 01:01:56,580
How can I help?

872
01:02:02,420 --> 01:02:04,719
Finish this.

873
01:02:06,520 --> 01:02:07,560
And?

874
01:02:08,560 --> 01:02:09,759
Let me finish this.

875
01:02:10,759 --> 01:02:11,799
Okay.

876
01:02:29,850 --> 01:02:31,580
- Did I get it on me again? - Yes, and on your first bite.

877
01:02:38,819 --> 01:02:40,119
Why does this make my heart race?

878
01:02:45,630 --> 01:02:46,630
I let you off.

879
01:02:47,860 --> 01:02:50,969
I was going to hold a grudge against you for running away last time.

880
01:03:02,810 --> 01:03:05,380
I'll drop by the bookstore to get some stuff I checked out.

881
01:03:07,250 --> 01:03:08,319
See you.

882
01:03:37,279 --> 01:03:38,650
It's a great layout for its size.

883
01:03:39,219 --> 01:03:42,619
The previous tenant kept it so clean.

884
01:03:43,250 --> 01:03:45,619
It's in incredible condition.

885
01:04:39,940 --> 01:04:42,350
Is my academy involved in this incident?

886
01:04:46,549 --> 01:04:49,650
Ms. Seo is a woman, so...

887
01:04:51,619 --> 01:04:54,790
You felt uncomfortable asking her about it.

888
01:04:55,589 --> 01:04:56,929
Because the words going around are smutty.

889
01:05:01,529 --> 01:05:03,369
Did Director Choi say she wasn't involved?

890
01:05:05,199 --> 01:05:06,540
She won't take questions.

891
01:05:07,239 --> 01:05:08,440
She said she had no intention of sharing...

892
01:05:08,710 --> 01:05:10,139
how she runs her business.

893
01:05:14,639 --> 01:05:16,909
When you said you'd join Choisun Academy,

894
01:05:18,580 --> 01:05:20,449
Ms. Seo once told me...

895
01:05:22,489 --> 01:05:25,960
that she would let you take her students if she could.

896
01:05:28,489 --> 01:05:30,330
She hates Choi Hyung Sun,

897
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:33,000
but she was relieved that the students have you...

898
01:05:33,630 --> 01:05:34,630
to learn from.

899
01:05:36,069 --> 01:05:38,139
I bet that's how Ms. Seo feels.

900
01:05:41,739 --> 01:05:42,810
That makes no sense.

901
01:05:43,409 --> 01:05:46,380
Those students must mean everything to her.

902
01:05:47,440 --> 01:05:48,549
Don't worry.

903
01:05:49,110 --> 01:05:51,080
She's thinking like crazy of a way to bring them back.

904
01:06:03,730 --> 01:06:04,799
It's nothing.

905
01:06:05,500 --> 01:06:06,730
You should get back to your class.

906
01:06:07,960 --> 01:06:09,699
- Yes. - Bye, then.

907
01:06:26,380 --> 01:06:27,380
Min Ji.

908
01:06:27,850 --> 01:06:29,850
Can I take a yellow chalk?

909
01:06:33,719 --> 01:06:36,060
- Mine hasn't arrived yet. - You can't.

910
01:06:37,630 --> 01:06:39,798
You have two.

911
01:06:39,799 --> 01:06:41,400
We need a lot of yellow today.

912
01:06:42,429 --> 01:06:43,869
You're not the teacher.

913
01:06:44,029 --> 01:06:45,699
I can tell by what section she'll teach.

914
01:06:47,469 --> 01:06:48,710
Then what about purple?

915
01:06:50,469 --> 01:06:51,480
No.

916
01:06:53,210 --> 01:06:54,739
I keep a special ledger for this.

917
01:06:57,310 --> 01:06:58,318
A ledger?

918
01:06:58,319 --> 01:07:01,549
I took note of all the times you took Ms. Seo's chalks.

919
01:07:01,750 --> 01:07:03,250
You took just the expensive ones.

920
01:07:04,619 --> 01:07:06,060
When did I just take the expensive...

921
01:07:08,460 --> 01:07:10,859
Did Hye Jin ask you to keep track of her chalk?

922
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:12,758
No, but if you take any more,

923
01:07:12,759 --> 01:07:14,500
I will start telling her.

924
01:07:15,529 --> 01:07:17,368
Min Ji. We're all family...

925
01:07:17,369 --> 01:07:19,440
- Hi. - Hello.

926
01:07:21,739 --> 01:07:23,738
Okay, Min Ji. I'll let you work.

927
01:07:23,739 --> 01:07:25,310
- Bye. - Hello.

928
01:07:26,380 --> 01:07:27,710
- Ms. Choi. - Yes?

929
01:07:28,779 --> 01:07:30,549
I forgot to bring my textbook.

930
01:07:30,949 --> 01:07:32,020
Goodness.

931
01:07:34,150 --> 01:07:35,150
Here.

932
01:07:36,449 --> 01:07:38,360
Oh, thank you.

933
01:07:38,819 --> 01:07:40,460
- Don't forget it next time. - Okay.

934
01:07:45,830 --> 01:07:48,029
(Vice-Director Woo Seung Hui)

935
01:07:56,670 --> 01:07:59,609
(Vice-Director Woo Seung Hui)

936
01:07:59,610 --> 01:08:01,679
A full barn is what makes people generous.

937
01:08:03,080 --> 01:08:05,179
Even if it looks fine on the outside,

938
01:08:05,750 --> 01:08:08,389
you can tell on the inside when a house...

939
01:08:09,089 --> 01:08:10,190
is about to go down.

940
01:08:11,520 --> 01:08:12,619
What do you mean?

941
01:08:14,259 --> 01:08:16,389
What? It's nothing.

942
01:08:21,770 --> 01:08:23,700
Why would she get so stingy over a piece of chalk?

943
01:08:29,339 --> 01:08:31,469
(Field Assistant)

944
01:08:36,910 --> 01:08:38,079
Hello, Ms. Woo.

945
01:08:38,780 --> 01:08:41,150
Hi, Min Ji.

946
01:08:42,219 --> 01:08:43,350
It's been a while.

947
01:08:44,889 --> 01:08:47,289
There's an opening in Mok-dong.

948
01:08:47,589 --> 01:08:48,789
I'm thinking of going there.

949
01:08:49,129 --> 01:08:50,160
Mok-dong?

950
01:08:51,230 --> 01:08:52,259
That's a nice place too.

951
01:08:52,860 --> 01:08:54,700
But why not go with Woo Seung Hui?

952
01:08:56,030 --> 01:08:57,829
I'm going to keep my options open.

953
01:08:59,169 --> 01:09:00,200
What about you?

954
01:09:03,410 --> 01:09:05,639
I'm going to talk to the director first.

955
01:09:08,249 --> 01:09:09,780
I'm a team leader,

956
01:09:10,079 --> 01:09:11,379
so I feel bad to jump at the first offer.

957
01:09:16,289 --> 01:09:18,249
Isn't today Ms. Kim's day off?

958
01:09:18,490 --> 01:09:19,490
It is.

959
01:09:22,459 --> 01:09:25,530
She had no intention of sharing how she runs her business.

960
01:09:33,139 --> 01:09:35,139
I'd like you to think about it carefully.

961
01:09:39,839 --> 01:09:43,008
The consultants say your classes are still stable...

962
01:09:43,009 --> 01:09:45,850
I'll teach until the end of this month.

963
01:09:49,950 --> 01:09:52,490
The director is looking for a solution too.

964
01:09:53,060 --> 01:09:55,160
I didn't make the decision flippantly.

965
01:09:56,360 --> 01:09:57,429
Sorry.

966
01:10:02,370 --> 01:10:03,429
I just...

967
01:10:04,799 --> 01:10:06,400
want to treat you to a meal.

968
01:10:07,240 --> 01:10:08,669
Would that be too uncomfortable?

969
01:10:10,839 --> 01:10:12,079
Did Ms. Woo...

970
01:10:13,310 --> 01:10:14,940
Did she promise you something?

971
01:10:16,280 --> 01:10:18,549
- What do you mean? - Did she say...

972
01:10:19,049 --> 01:10:20,549
she could give you...

973
01:10:22,719 --> 01:10:24,089
my teaching materials?

974
01:10:26,860 --> 01:10:27,919
Did she say...

975
01:10:30,530 --> 01:10:33,400
I wasn't just going down, but that I was crashing and burning?

976
01:10:34,329 --> 01:10:36,329
- Well... - Did she say...

977
01:10:37,230 --> 01:10:39,570
there's really not one ounce of hope...

978
01:10:40,200 --> 01:10:41,270
left for this academy?

979
01:10:43,539 --> 01:10:44,539
Yes.

980
01:10:47,110 --> 01:10:49,780
She said we should all escape soon.

981
01:11:31,350 --> 01:11:34,959
(The Midnight Romance in Hagwon)

982
01:11:35,389 --> 01:11:36,459
I heard.

983
01:11:36,660 --> 01:11:39,230
You're going through the worst time of your life.

984
01:11:39,360 --> 01:11:42,329
There's a part-time opening that provides a scholarship.

985
01:11:42,429 --> 01:11:43,469
Do you want to go?

986
01:11:43,929 --> 01:11:44,929
I was crazy.

987
01:11:45,799 --> 01:11:46,999
I was out of it.

988
01:11:47,240 --> 01:11:49,469
What Choi Hyung Sun really wants is Seo Hye Jin.

989
01:11:50,039 --> 01:11:51,780
Is that your idea, Myeong Jun?

990
01:11:52,539 --> 01:11:53,910
Seo Hye Jin's here.

991
01:11:54,839 --> 01:11:55,850
Ta-da.

992
01:11:56,150 --> 01:11:58,579
Do you think I'll be able to make a comeback?

993
01:11:58,820 --> 01:11:59,918
How am I going to stay with you...

994
01:11:59,919 --> 01:12:00,919
for the rest of my life if you're like this?

995
01:12:00,920 --> 01:12:02,889
I can't imagine being without him by my side.

996
01:12:03,520 --> 01:12:04,820
I'll give you everything you ask.
